31/10/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia and Montenegro confirmed a mutual desire to strengthen bilateral ties and co-operation during a visit by Montenegrin Foreign Minister Miodrag Vlahovic to Zagreb on Saturday (30 October).
Meeting with Vlahovic, Croatian President Stipe Mesic also pledged his country's support and assistance in the process of Euro-Atlantic integration.
On 15 November, Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader is expected to pay a formal visit to Serbia-Montenegro.
(Danas, B92, HINA - 30/10/04)
